review_blob: Dark brown with a small head. Smells of candi sugar. Notes of caramel, dry leaves, candi sugar, butterscotch, a hint of red fruit, some latte. Enjoyable beer, finish is the same with walnut, a bit disappointing though in length
beer_name: Vossen met de Meynen Six O Six (606)

review_blob: Clear amber if you dont pour the bottom. Good fluffy head. Malty with dry leaves, spices, orange bitters, sugar. Full mouthfeel and medium bitter finish
Clear amber with excellent carbonation and a nice fluffy head. Grapefruit right from the start, with lemon zest , dry leaves, some earth, walnuts. Long bitter dry finish. Nice IPA
beer_name: De Dochter van de Korenaar Extase

review_blob: Orange amber with a small head. A bit of caramel, honey, malt, funk. Some lemon syrup in the finish, but watery.
Cloudy orange with a nice head. Traditional full taste with grains, sugar and yeast. Nothing much more
Pale straw blonde with a medium had. Not much carbonation, bit creamy. Slightly more hoppy than a regular ale, finish is dry and mineral. Not bad but still watery
Pitch black with a beige head. Burnt caramel in the nose. Chocolate, latte, a hint of red fruit roasted malts. More dryness in the long finish.
Yellow, slightly hazy with a small head. Some hops in the nose. Taste is more malt, sugar, earth, walnut, a hint of fruit. Slightly dryer finish with some white sugar, licorice. Nice beer

Nice clear golden colour with a foamy head and lots of carbonation. Dirt, earth, rotten leaves, orange peel, some sugar, alcohol. Also some metal and paint unfortunately. Medium tingly finish with too much alcohol
Between amber and yellow with a small head. Heavy citrus in the nose. Earthy, heavy malt, yeast, lemon zeste, alcohol, pine, grapefruit. Long earthen finish with a bit too much alcohol
Dark brown with a small head. Caramel, candy sugar, mineral. Medium finish with some mineral dryness. Not too sweet and sticky. Well made but not exceptional
Red brown without foam head. No carbonation, flat. Sour and a bit sticky, some cherries and lemon. Citric finish
Dark amber with a small head. Ok carbonation, little taste. Some malt and bread but mostly water. Short finish

Pitch black with almost no head. Full body with dark malts, spices, candy sugar, alcohol, cough drop. Some jagermeister without the stickiness. More of the oak in the finish, a hint of read fruit there too. Long finish

Reddish brown with an off white quickly diminishing head. Pretty sour at first with lots of berries, then some more malt, earth, minerals and a hint of vanilla and chestnut. Notions of wood into the dryer medium finish.
Hazy blond with a creamy head. Malty with a mild bitterness. Little body, short finish
Hazy blond with a small foam top. Citrus fruit, white sugar, malt,a little hop. Not very complex but enjoyable. Bit too sweet in the finish
Sour grapefruit nose. Cloudy yellow with quickly receding head. Sour and funky, earth after a while, citrus fruit, malt, lemon sorbet. Sweeter finish but also sour and bitter. Quite interesting
beer_name: Troubadour Magma Special Edition 2015 Triple Spiked Brett

review_blob: Excellent nose with a bunch of citrus. Malt and double hop, lots of taste for such little ABV. One sided as most double IPA, but good craftsmanship. Long dry finish
Dark brown with a beige head. Excellent citrus smell. Dark malts, hops, citrus fruit, dry wood, walnut, red fruit. Long bitter finish. Prefect marriage of hop and dark malt
Pitch black with creamy head. Very malty, coffee grind, port, burnt caramel. Too much alcohol in the finish. Tingly. Quite dry there too
beer_name: De Dochter van de Korenaar Sans Pardon

review_blob: Pitch dark with a good head. Initial strong whiskey taste. Then creamy, coffee grind, roasted malts, red fruit. Long finish, port taste. Whiskey too dominant
beer_name: Inglorious Quad Whisky Barrel Aged - batch 1 Belgian Owl

review_blob: Deep brown colour with a good fluffy head. Roasted malt, brown sugar, cheap coffee, some amaretto. No full body though, a bit watery. Bitter but mostly sweet pleasant finish with a bit too much alcohol
Dark with a beige head. Not much nose. Pretty bland at first. Malt, candi sugar, raisins, mineral, nuts follow. Nice finish with a bit more sourness and cask. Not bad.
beer_name: Van Den Bossche Buffalo Belgian Stout

review_blob: Clear gold with a lasting top. Mostly water with some bitterness, malt and sugar. OK finish with a dry bitterness and mineral water
Blonde with a nice creamy head. Oily texture, bread, hay, candi sugar but mostly hops. Bit too one sided. Medium finish with some earth in the bitters
Yellow with a nice head. Very full body. Earth, banana, malt. Long finish with some alcohol
Hazy orange,nice head. Creamy. Orange, malt. Medium body. Mineral finish, medium bitterness, well balanced
Orange with little head. Smells of mango. Lots of hops. Dry leaves, earth malt. Medium body. Long finish with some white sugar and more bitters. A bit too little fruit
beer_name: Green Flash West Coast IPA (European Edition)

review_blob: Hazy orange with a fluffy head. Bread, lemon zest, hops. Sweetness dominated by the bitters. Long bitter finish
Cloudy amber with a beige head. Malty, caramel and fresh red fruit. Bit thin. Short watery finish with the alcohol coming through. Bit disappointing
Dark brown with red notes. Roasted malt, raisins, dried red fruit, some wild sourness, red cherry, wood. Quite a bit of alcohol. Medium finish in which there sugars take over. Enjoyable beer
Cloudy amber, good head. Orange and some orange peel, earth, glucose, malt. Quite a bit of alcohol comes through. Long hot finish, sweet sour and some bitter
Hazy amber with a lot of fizz. Floral hoppy smell, some oranges at first. Quite some bitterness, wallnut, dry malt and dry leaves. Long finish, dry malty but maybe a bit sticky dry after a while

Dark brown beer with a small beige head. Smell of red fruit and sugared creamy coffee. Caramel, red fruit, spices, candi sugar, latte. Looking finish with a bit more bitterness and white sugar. Well balanced
Hazy orange brown with a small off white head. Yeasty nose. Burnt caramel, roasted malts, white sugar, bit of orange peel, some butterscotch, raisin. Some mineral taste in the finish. Well rounded
Hazy yellow with a quickly diminishing head. Very yeasty, citrus, sugar. Medium finish with lemon and sugar
Amber with a nice foam head. Hoppy grapefruit nose. Bitter, malty, citrus, some earth. A bit of metal in the finish it seems though
beer_name: Praris IPA - No Hops No Glory

review_blob: Hazy straw with a nice foam top. Fresh taste, some coriander, citrus, malt. Medium finish, bit watery and mineral. Nice white beer
Dark beer with a small head. Dark malts, spices, nuts, some grapes, some alcohol as well. Not too sweet, dry and mineral in the finish. Pleasant beer
Clear gold with a foamy head. Fizzy. Lots of yeast, malt and some sugar. Dry wood, leaves, some earth. A bit of alcohol. Yeast in the finish and white sugar. Pretty average
Cloudy yellow, gushing from the bottle and with a very fizzy head. Mild lemon, a bit of sugar, hay, spruce, mineral. Light tingling finish
Hazy gold, foamy top. Some earth, malt, yeast, but way too sweet. Cant see why it would be labeled speciale
Amber, very frisky with a bubbly head. Nice hoppy scent. High bitterness, Lemon zest, some salt licorice, malt, alcohol, zoethout. Dry wooden finish. Bit one sided focus on bitterness
Amber brown with an of white head. Malt, some red fruit, cough syrup, salt licorice a bit, some distant red fruit. Some pleasant dryness in the finish, but also some alcohol

Black with a light brown head. Fantastic hoppy nose, floral and citric. Oily mouth feel. Full taste of roasted malts, cappuccino, spices, candi sugar, coffee grind. Long finish with some more white sugar, mineral. Incredible taste for such low alcohol percentage

Very disappointing. Bought this thinking it was Brugse Tripel which has a much fuller taste, this is just an uninspired brew. Looks good, between amber and gold with a firm head. A lot of carbonation, a bit of malt, some earth. Short finish
Clear straw with good carbonation and firm head. Typical tripel. Some lemon peel, white sugar, yeast, a bit spicy. Nothing original but nice finish and good craftsmanship
Dark brown with a reddish tint. Almost no head. Spicy nose, plums. Aromas of wine, burnt caramel, malt, sour cherries. Quite an earthy finish with a lot of alcohol

Hazy amber with a foamy head. Nice hoppy nose. Candi, orange, malty, also some earth, dry leaves and a bit funky. More sugar, alcohol and a dry stickiness in the finish. Not entirely convinced, had better ipas before
beer_name: De Dochter van de Korenaar Crime Passionnel
